AWS Bedrock for Copilot
=======================

This software is a fork of amazon-bedrock-copilot-chat:

    Project:   amazon-bedrock-copilot-chat
    Author:    Konstantin Vyatkin (@tinovyatkin)
    Source:    https://github.com/tinovyatkin/amazon-bedrock-copilot-chat
    License:   MIT License
    Copyright: (c) 2024 Konstantin Vyatkin

All foundational work -- the VSCode LanguageModelChatProvider integration,
Amazon Bedrock streaming, message/tool conversion, AWS authentication, and
the overall extension architecture -- was authored by Konstantin Vyatkin in
the upstream project. This fork preserves and builds on that work.

Modifications in this fork
--------------------------

    Project:   aws-bedrock-for-copilot
    Maintainer: Rangan (@rangan2510)
    Source:    https://github.com/rangan2510/aws-bedrock-for-copilot
    License:   MIT License (same as upstream)
    Copyright: (c) 2026 Rangan and contributors to this fork

This fork adds, among other things:

  * Claude Opus 4.7 support (adaptive thinking, deprecated temperature
    parameter handling)
  * Claude Haiku 4.5 extended thinking support
  * Corrected thinking modes and token limits for Claude 4.x generations
  * Expanded, CLI-verified capability profiles for 80+ models across 14
    providers
  * Graceful fallback when a model returns unparseable tool_use JSON
  * `reasoning_effort` support for non-Anthropic reasoning models
    (OpenAI gpt-oss, DeepSeek V3.2, Moonshot Kimi, Qwen3, GLM, MiniMax)
    via a single `aws-bedrock-for-copilot.reasoningEffort` setting
  * Vendor-namespaced settings (`anthropic.thinking.*`,
    `anthropic.context1M.enabled`, etc.) with backward-compat reads of
    the legacy flat keys
  * Region dropdown in the Settings UI populated from the known set of
    AWS Bedrock regions
  * Capability-aware tooltips and inline detail strings in the model
    picker (context window, output, thinking/reasoning mode, vision)
  * LEGACY models surfaced with a warning prefix instead of being
    silently filtered, so users can opt in with full visibility
  * Parallel extension identity (vendor "aws-bedrock-for-copilot" with its
    own config namespace), so it can be installed alongside the upstream
    extension

The full list of changes is in CHANGELOG.md, under the
"Fork changelog" section.

Relationship to upstream
------------------------

This is a friendly fork, not a hostile one. It exists to unblock users
during periods of reduced upstream activity. Bugfixes and improvements
that are not specific to the parallel-install identity rename are
periodically offered upstream as pull requests. If the upstream project
resumes active maintenance, the intent is to merge changes back and
sunset this fork.

If this extension is useful to you, please also star and watch the
upstream repository:

    https://github.com/tinovyatkin/amazon-bedrock-copilot-chat

